snippet.textDisplay: Came across the song few days back and felt like how did i miss this fantastic work. Each line of the spendid lyrics links to the history of Islam, the prophets of Allah, pious and righteous servants and the angels. If you enjoyed it even without having knowledge of Islam, just pick up a part of the lyrics and find out why it used phrases like nooh ki kashti or rab-e sahaba, wall of dhul qarnayn etc and their importance and you will surely love it more. And the day you start understanding the message behind these stories and will get to know about the prophets and your creator and about your existence , you will experience something which can't be described.
